<br>
I have played many warriors of many races and one thing i like doing is not playing the same type of warrior again and again, so i feel quite happy to answer this questions as best i can.<br>
<br>
STA - Over 110 if you can get it, that gives you a nice amount of hp.<br>
<br>
STR - 90+ for carrying armour, 100+ for carry wepons and spares 110+ for carrying wepons spares and misc items.<br>
<br>
AGI - 75+ total, 80+ for above average performance, 90+ for quality dodging and actually takeing damage off hitts to ya self.<br>
<br>
DEX - for hitting more often, high dex vs low dex makes such a difference, you crit and cripple more you get more Higher/average damage hits landing. NEVER let dex get below 75, 80 is what you want it at base lv, 85 makes a world of difference and at 90 you notice the amount of crits a damn lot more than a base 75.<br>
<br>
Now for a troll i would think of what wepons you are going to be using, your high str gives you an advantage for the first 12 lvs as you reach your damage cap sooner, at lv21 the others will catch you up and you will only out damage them by 1-3 points per hit at best. (wich is why small race dual wield.)<br>
Since a troll highs STR has you covered until the 2 handed wepons loose out to dual wielding you must prepare for that... so i say put ya DEX to 80 base, you will notice the effects later on when dual wielding, you can get lots of DEX gear by any decednt STA gear is normally low ac and hard to get and find, once you have base dex of 80 pump stamina wich will give you hitpoints in the longrun. (you can never go wrong with STA, but at a certain limit it is not worth compromising STA for weeker stats)<br>
<br>
